            <div type="edition" subtype="ogham" xml:space="preserve">
                <div type="textpart" n="1" xml:lang="pgl-Ogam">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up"/><persName><name nymRef="#magladubracu">ᚋᚐᚌᚂ<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown"/>ᚇᚒᚁᚏ<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown"/></name>
                    <lb n="2" style="text-direction:down"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown"/>ᚊᚔ<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown"/></persName>                
                </ab>
              </div>
            </div>      
            <div type="edition" subtype="transliteration" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="pgl">
                    <ab>
                        <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up"/><persName><name nymRef="#magladubracu">MAGL<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown"/>DUBR<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown"/></name>
                        <lb n="2" style="text-direction:down"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown"/>QI<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown"/></persName> 
                    </ab>
               </div>
            <div type="edition" subtype="roman" xml:space="preserve">
                    <div type="textpart" n="2" xml:lang="pgl-Latn">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><w><hi rend="ligature">ET</hi></w><w>SIN<hi rend="ligature">GN</hi>O</w><w>CR
                    <lb n="2"/>UCIS</w><w>IN</w><w>ILLAM</w>
                    <lb n="3"/><w>FINGSI</w><w>ROGO</w>
                    <lb n="4"/><w>OMNI</w><w>BUSAM</w>
                    <lb n="5"/><w>MULAN<hi rend="ligature">TI</hi>BUS</w>
                    <lb n="6"/><w>IBI</w><w><hi rend="ligature">EX</hi>ORENT</w>
                    <lb n="7"/><w>PRO</w><w>ANIM<hi rend="ligature">AE</hi></w>
                    <lb n="8"/><persName><name>CATUOCONI</name></persName>
                </ab>
               </div>
            </div>   
            <div type="apparatus">
                <p></p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <div type="textpart" n="1">
                     <p>Ogham: <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up"/>'MAGLI<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown"/>DUBR<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown"/>
                        <lb n="2" style="text-direction:down"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown"/>QI<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown"/>'</p>
                </div>
               </div>
              <div type="textpart" n="2">
                  <p>Latin: 'With the sign of the cross I fashioned on that [?] I ask all walking there that they pray for the soul of <persName xml:lang="pgl">Catuoconus</persName>'</p>
              </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                        <p><q>The surviving ogam letters suggest a compound personal name: (i) MAGL[-]DUBR, and (ii) -QI-, which could be part of <foreign xml:lang="sga"><ref target="https://dil.ie/31166">maqi</ref></foreign>... The inscription is unlikely to be other than Irish, in view of the use of ogam and the presence of Q... Both DUBAR[CUNAS] and... DUBR[ACUNAS].. seem possible restorations, both being possible spellings of Old Irish <foreign xml:lang="sga"><ref target="https://dil.ie/17278">doborchú</ref></foreign>, gen. <foreign xml:lang="sga">doborchon</foreign>, 'water-dog, otter'</q> (Edwards 2007, 296).</p>
                        <p>CATUOCONI is later Welsh <foreign xml:lang="wlm">Cadwgan</foreign>, a compound of <foreign xml:lang="owl">cad</foreign>, 'battle', and <foreign xml:lang="owl">g(w)ogawn</foreign>, 'glory', with a Latin genitive ending added. Both the lettering and the content of the Latin inscription suggest a high level of literacy, though case endings are not always correct... The meaning of <foreign xml:lang="la">illam</foreign><q>...cannot be satisfactorily resolved. It has also been cogently argued that some of the unusual features of the Caldy Island 1 inscription can be explained because it is set to metre in the form of rhythmic syllabic adonics, of which it may be the earliest known example</q> (Edwards 2007, 298).</p>
            </div>
